WEBVTT



00:00:08.321 --> 00:00:13.034
If you are ever hurt

00:00:13.785 --> 00:00:19.040
And find yourself discouraged

00:00:19.124 --> 00:00:24.212
I will always be by your side

00:00:24.796 --> 00:00:27.340
To hold you up by your shoulders

00:00:27.423 --> 00:00:29.134
What was that song again?

00:00:30.552 --> 00:00:32.887
So, what could it be?

00:00:33.805 --> 00:00:35.515
Oh, I got it!

00:00:36.182 --> 00:00:37.392
Yes?

00:00:37.475 --> 00:00:38.601
"Tomorrow"!

00:00:40.103 --> 00:00:42.355
-Wrong!
-Stop that!

00:00:42.438 --> 00:00:44.440
Hey, that's my phone!

00:00:44.524 --> 00:00:46.109
Why are you filming?

00:00:46.609 --> 00:00:49.654
Carrying the hopes…

00:00:49.737 --> 00:00:52.407
Come on, ten days left! Go, go!

00:00:53.408 --> 00:00:54.367
Harder!

00:00:54.450 --> 00:00:56.452
-Go, Nakaji!
-You're doing great!

00:00:56.536 --> 00:00:57.579
Oh, man.

00:00:57.662 --> 00:00:59.289
All right, let's go!

00:01:00.331 --> 00:01:02.542
Seiichi, want a drink? Here!

00:01:04.460 --> 00:01:07.463
Check the breakouts, forecheck,
and backcheck with your line.

00:01:07.547 --> 00:01:09.007
Got it.

00:01:09.090 --> 00:01:10.466
Okay, good work, everyone.

00:01:10.550 --> 00:01:12.135
That's all for practice today.

00:01:12.218 --> 00:01:13.595
Seio! One, two, three!

00:01:14.929 --> 00:01:17.056
-Have another bowl, okay?
-Seriously?

00:01:17.140 --> 00:01:19.475
The balance and quantity
of carbs and protein is--

00:01:19.559 --> 00:01:21.436
Oh, shut up already.

00:01:21.519 --> 00:01:24.314
Weren't you gonna take
Arata's starting spot before graduation?

00:01:24.397 --> 00:01:26.232
Of course I am! Definitely.

00:01:26.900 --> 00:01:28.276
I'm looking forward to it.

00:01:28.776 --> 00:01:31.821
Man, this guy doesn't feel
threatened at all.

00:01:32.405 --> 00:01:36.034
Hey, Arata. You're coming
to the mixer this time, aren't you?

00:01:37.160 --> 00:01:39.120
Um, well…

00:01:39.204 --> 00:01:41.915
Come on, I'm begging you. Please come.

00:01:41.998 --> 00:01:45.168
-The girls would eagerly join if you came.
-Yeah.

00:01:45.251 --> 00:01:46.836
We're up against pageant girls.

00:01:46.920 --> 00:01:47.795
That's right.

00:01:47.879 --> 00:01:49.547
That cheerleader's coming too.

00:01:49.631 --> 00:01:50.965
-She's super cute.
-Yeah.

00:01:51.049 --> 00:01:52.467
-Seriously.
-It'll be awesome.

00:01:52.550 --> 00:01:54.427
Oh, Ryu. You're coming too.

00:01:54.510 --> 00:01:56.054
I never said I was going.

00:01:56.137 --> 00:01:57.472
Why not? Come on.

00:02:03.770 --> 00:02:05.480
That was a foul just now!

00:02:12.612 --> 00:02:15.490
Hey, Arata!

00:02:15.990 --> 00:02:17.492
What are you doing?

00:02:18.117 --> 00:02:19.202
What is it?

00:02:19.285 --> 00:02:21.579
-Why are you making that face?
-What?

00:02:22.080 --> 00:02:24.040
Hello, this is Narutaki.

00:02:24.123 --> 00:02:24.958
Mm-hmm?

00:02:25.041 --> 00:02:26.834
-Having love trouble?
-Nah.

00:02:27.794 --> 00:02:28.753
Get off me!

00:02:28.836 --> 00:02:29.879
Ryu!

00:02:31.631 --> 00:02:33.800
Ryu! Arata!

00:02:33.883 --> 00:02:35.969
Arata, are your legs holding up?

00:02:36.052 --> 00:02:38.012
-I've got energy to spare.
-Okay.

00:02:38.596 --> 00:02:41.140
-Did someone ask you out again?
-Come on.

00:02:41.224 --> 00:02:44.018
-You're so popular!
-What? Jeez, stop it.

00:02:44.102 --> 00:02:45.478
SEIO UNIV. 3
AODAI UNIV. 3

00:02:56.114 --> 00:02:58.074
I know someone who's always liked you.

00:02:58.574 --> 00:02:59.450
Who?

00:03:01.869 --> 00:03:02.745
Me.

00:03:03.746 --> 00:03:04.580
Huh?

00:03:19.887 --> 00:03:21.055
Shoot!

00:03:23.808 --> 00:03:24.934
I have feelings…

00:03:28.980 --> 00:03:30.023
for you.

00:03:30.898 --> 00:03:32.525
SEIO UNIV. 4
AODAI UNIV. 3

00:04:13.441 --> 00:04:18.321
SEIICHI: WHERE ARE YOU?
PLEASE REPLY. NO ONE BLAMES YOU.

00:04:19.238 --> 00:04:22.367
You said you were friends!
Did you lie to your father? Wait, Lukas!

00:04:22.450 --> 00:04:25.953
I knew this would happen!
That's why I had to lie!

00:04:28.289 --> 00:04:29.374
Stop it!

00:04:29.457 --> 00:04:32.168
It's bad for the family
that my son is gay!

00:04:32.251 --> 00:04:34.837
We can't even go to church!

00:04:34.921 --> 00:04:37.965
-You only care about yourself, Dad!
-We're leaving.

00:04:38.049 --> 00:04:40.009
I'd rather die if I can't be with him!

00:04:40.093 --> 00:04:41.469
God will not forgive you!

00:04:41.552 --> 00:04:42.929
Damn the church!

00:04:43.012 --> 00:04:46.307
Hey, I got one for you too, Ryu.

00:04:46.808 --> 00:04:48.059
Come with me.

00:04:48.768 --> 00:04:49.602
What is it?

00:04:50.228 --> 00:04:51.354
A boxing match ticket.

00:04:52.188 --> 00:04:54.148
Sure, I'll go with you.

00:04:54.649 --> 00:04:55.733
But why boxing?

00:04:56.984 --> 00:05:01.072
There's a competition coming up at school.
Winning could really open doors for me.

00:05:01.155 --> 00:05:03.491
And my theme is

00:05:04.367 --> 00:05:05.868
fists and beauty.

00:05:08.246 --> 00:05:09.497
Fists?

00:05:09.580 --> 00:05:10.998
And beauty.

00:05:11.499 --> 00:05:12.333
And beauty.

00:05:13.251 --> 00:05:15.336
But hey, is this really okay?

00:05:15.420 --> 00:05:16.546
What is?

00:05:16.629 --> 00:05:20.508
Ice hockey.
You're missing so much practice.

00:05:21.175 --> 00:05:23.261
I've been playing since middle school.

00:05:24.220 --> 00:05:26.597
I need to refresh myself once in a while.

00:05:28.474 --> 00:05:31.936
You call this refreshing?
All you're doing is lazing around.

00:05:32.437 --> 00:05:35.940
Lazing around overseas.
That's refreshing to me.

00:05:37.150 --> 00:05:40.653
You'll get flabby before you know it.
Especially your upper arms.

00:05:41.237 --> 00:05:42.822
Flabby?

00:05:56.377 --> 00:05:58.838
-Cheers!
-Cheers.

00:05:59.338 --> 00:06:00.256
Yeah.

00:06:17.565 --> 00:06:21.402
That's true.
Stories definitely do bring in money.

00:06:21.486 --> 00:06:22.695
I'm glad you're here.

00:06:25.948 --> 00:06:28.576
Was the hotel to your liking?

00:06:29.702 --> 00:06:30.828
Yes.

00:06:33.331 --> 00:06:34.749
Oh, here.

00:06:37.710 --> 00:06:39.253
Your advance payment.

00:06:45.176 --> 00:06:49.013
I trust you. Do a good job, okay?

00:06:49.597 --> 00:06:50.640
Yes, sir.

00:07:10.952 --> 00:07:12.578
-I'll go get a drink.
-Sure.

00:07:38.938 --> 00:07:39.772
Here.

00:07:41.607 --> 00:07:42.942
-So, Layla was saying…
-Yeah?

00:07:43.025 --> 00:07:45.695
She says you should check out her work.

00:07:46.612 --> 00:07:47.446
Check them out?

00:07:48.114 --> 00:07:50.992
Yeah, she said
you should take a good look.

00:07:51.075 --> 00:07:54.745
Layla makes sculptures,
using human sin as her theme.

00:07:54.829 --> 00:07:56.163
I see.

00:08:02.920 --> 00:08:06.090
They're being displayed
at a church near my place.

00:08:06.173 --> 00:08:09.176
Wanna drop by together
before the boxing match?

00:08:09.677 --> 00:08:11.554
Yeah, sounds good.

00:08:30.114 --> 00:08:33.826
At the time, I couldn't say anything.

00:08:35.369 --> 00:08:36.787
I couldn't move.

00:08:37.788 --> 00:08:41.917
Learning how I truly felt

00:08:42.668 --> 00:08:43.628
scared me.

00:08:43.711 --> 00:08:46.339
Hey, Arata!

00:08:46.422 --> 00:08:47.673
What are you doing?

00:08:48.174 --> 00:08:49.467
What is it?

00:08:49.550 --> 00:08:51.802
-Why are you making that face?
-What?

00:08:52.303 --> 00:08:54.305
Hello, this is Narutaki.

00:08:54.388 --> 00:08:55.222
Mm-hmm?

00:08:55.306 --> 00:08:57.683
-Having love trouble?
-Nah.

00:09:01.270 --> 00:09:02.605
By the way, that mixer…

00:09:03.856 --> 00:09:04.815
Are you going?

00:09:04.899 --> 00:09:08.152
Well, I'm not great
with that kind of stuff.

00:09:08.653 --> 00:09:09.820
Are you?

00:09:10.905 --> 00:09:13.032
-No.
-I see.

00:09:13.532 --> 00:09:14.617
Oh.

00:09:14.700 --> 00:09:17.453
-I know! Did someone ask you out again?
-Come on.

00:09:17.536 --> 00:09:20.081
-You're so popular!
-Jeez, stop it.

00:09:25.795 --> 00:09:27.755
-You know what?
-What?

00:09:29.006 --> 00:09:30.925
I know someone who's always liked you.

00:09:31.008 --> 00:09:32.385
Who?

00:09:34.845 --> 00:09:35.763
Me.

00:09:37.306 --> 00:09:38.265
Huh?

00:09:43.437 --> 00:09:44.522
Like I said…

00:09:49.985 --> 00:09:51.237
I have feelings…

00:09:53.781 --> 00:09:54.824
for you.

00:10:04.500 --> 00:10:05.793
Shocking, isn't it?

00:10:24.145 --> 00:10:26.355
Sorry to drop this on you before a match.

00:10:26.981 --> 00:10:27.857
It's fine.

00:10:32.903 --> 00:10:36.115
It's not like I want
an answer or anything.

00:10:40.786 --> 00:10:42.037
I just wanted you…

00:10:44.123 --> 00:10:47.877
to know how I feel.

00:10:51.422 --> 00:10:52.923
That alone…

00:10:55.342 --> 00:10:58.053
is enough to change my world.

00:11:05.770 --> 00:11:06.771
Well…

00:11:07.480 --> 00:11:09.815
Good night, then.

00:11:11.025 --> 00:11:11.942
Yeah.

00:11:14.528 --> 00:11:15.571
You know what?

00:11:17.698 --> 00:11:19.867
I know someone who's always liked you.

00:11:19.950 --> 00:11:21.035
Who?

00:11:22.077 --> 00:11:23.078
Me.

00:13:42.259 --> 00:13:43.302
I…

00:13:45.471 --> 00:13:46.597
I…

00:13:52.353 --> 00:13:53.812
I cast aside…

00:13:56.440 --> 00:13:57.983
his feelings.

00:14:04.698 --> 00:14:05.741
I'm…

00:14:08.744 --> 00:14:12.331
I'm… the worst.

00:14:19.672 --> 00:14:20.798
I was scared.

00:14:24.343 --> 00:14:26.303
Scared of being liked.

00:14:29.932 --> 00:14:31.892
I'm sorry.

00:14:32.893 --> 00:14:36.563
I'm sorry.

00:14:38.148 --> 00:14:40.943
I'm sorry.

00:14:49.868 --> 00:14:50.869
Dammit.

00:14:51.954 --> 00:14:53.998
Why is it always me? Why?

00:14:54.498 --> 00:14:55.541
Wait!

00:14:56.959 --> 00:14:58.377
Hey, wait!

00:15:46.258 --> 00:15:47.801
I get it.

00:16:03.734 --> 00:16:04.735
I'm sorry.

00:16:05.778 --> 00:16:07.571
Your feelings…

00:16:09.323 --> 00:16:10.699
And your life…

00:16:11.241 --> 00:16:12.701
I ruined all of it.

00:16:14.161 --> 00:16:15.245
Hey!

00:16:16.705 --> 00:16:17.706
Hey!

00:16:25.380 --> 00:16:27.633
Arata, I'm sorry.

00:16:32.638 --> 00:16:35.349
Ryu!

00:16:35.432 --> 00:16:37.893
Oh, thank goodness.

00:16:39.978 --> 00:16:41.021
Did…

00:16:43.941 --> 00:16:45.943
Did somebody save me?

00:16:47.986 --> 00:16:49.029
Yeah.

00:16:49.113 --> 00:16:54.159
You were found unconscious
with another man.

00:16:54.243 --> 00:16:58.539
But it looks like
he slipped out of the hospital room.

00:17:01.500 --> 00:17:02.876
I see.

00:17:47.921 --> 00:17:50.924
So, how are you feeling?

00:17:51.717 --> 00:17:52.843
Same as always.

00:17:53.510 --> 00:17:54.970
Huh? What are you doing?

00:17:56.346 --> 00:17:58.307
Nothing.

00:17:59.683 --> 00:18:01.476
You're reading manga again.

00:18:03.353 --> 00:18:05.272
Shut up.

00:18:06.690 --> 00:18:09.484
You really love that stuff, don't you?

00:18:11.111 --> 00:18:12.446
Is that so wrong?

00:18:15.449 --> 00:18:17.159
So, how's Berlin?

00:18:27.669 --> 00:18:28.712
Just normal.

00:18:47.814 --> 00:18:49.316
Do you have a minute?

00:18:54.863 --> 00:18:56.156
Um…

00:18:56.949 --> 00:18:59.910
I'm sorry I've been keeping quiet.

00:19:02.329 --> 00:19:05.082
I put you through all this worry too.

00:19:07.292 --> 00:19:08.335
It's fine.

00:19:10.170 --> 00:19:11.546
I'll be honest.

00:19:15.676 --> 00:19:17.052
I ran away.

00:19:18.387 --> 00:19:19.429
From Japan.

00:19:21.765 --> 00:19:22.808
What?

00:19:32.693 --> 00:19:33.694
Here.

00:19:40.575 --> 00:19:42.035
Can I watch it?

00:19:42.119 --> 00:19:43.120
Yeah.

00:19:51.712 --> 00:19:52.838
I have feelings…

00:19:56.717 --> 00:19:57.801
for you.

00:20:01.054 --> 00:20:02.097
What?

00:20:13.942 --> 00:20:15.235
Shocking, isn't it?

00:20:33.962 --> 00:20:35.088
What's wrong?

00:20:37.132 --> 00:20:38.175
Nothing.

00:20:51.146 --> 00:20:52.189
Hello?

00:20:52.272 --> 00:20:55.776
Hi. Uh, are you alone right now?

00:20:55.859 --> 00:20:58.445
Yeah. I think Seiichi's taking a bath.

00:20:58.945 --> 00:20:59.905
Oh.

00:21:00.572 --> 00:21:02.657
Um, what about Arata?

00:21:04.743 --> 00:21:05.786
Huh?

00:21:05.869 --> 00:21:11.249
Oh, uh, you were walking with him
by the riverside earlier, right?

00:21:14.211 --> 00:21:15.295
So what?

00:21:15.837 --> 00:21:20.300
Oh, well, um…

00:21:21.134 --> 00:21:24.721
I was wondering if he asked you out.

00:21:25.680 --> 00:21:26.723
What?

00:21:27.307 --> 00:21:30.102
I mean, it just had that vibe.

00:21:30.185 --> 00:21:35.065
You know, I kind of had a hunch
that maybe Arata swings that way.

00:21:37.192 --> 00:21:39.486
So, um…

00:21:41.154 --> 00:21:42.531
Are you guys dating?

00:21:43.031 --> 00:21:44.908
No, obviously not.

00:21:45.867 --> 00:21:48.954
Sorry. I didn't mean it in a weird way.

00:21:49.037 --> 00:21:52.749
I'm not homophobic or anything,
so it's totally okay with me.

00:21:54.292 --> 00:21:55.544
Well, you know…

00:21:57.838 --> 00:21:58.713
You know, it's…

00:21:58.797 --> 00:22:03.593
Oh, uh… I get it.
You don't swing that way, right?

00:22:04.719 --> 00:22:08.098
Um, well… Sorry about this, really.

00:22:08.682 --> 00:22:10.267
-Bye, then.
-No, I…

00:22:21.194 --> 00:22:23.321
I seriously didn't realize.

00:22:23.864 --> 00:22:26.324
Sorry I invited you to mixers and stuff.

00:22:26.408 --> 00:22:27.826
That was insensitive of me.

00:22:27.909 --> 00:22:28.743
Oh, come on!

00:22:28.827 --> 00:22:31.705
You were totally using Arata
to get the girls to come.

00:22:31.788 --> 00:22:33.790
-That's true!
-We're… You know?

00:22:33.874 --> 00:22:36.376
-We're fine with that stuff.
-Totally.

00:22:36.460 --> 00:22:37.294
Hi.

00:22:38.587 --> 00:22:41.006
-Morning!
-Morning.

00:22:52.267 --> 00:22:55.228
Well, I'll head out first.

00:22:55.312 --> 00:22:56.813
-Okay.
-See you.

00:23:02.736 --> 00:23:06.531
I didn't mean to out him or anything.

00:23:07.324 --> 00:23:11.119
But I thought we needed to
accept Arata for who he is.

00:23:11.203 --> 00:23:12.954
Accept him?

00:23:15.165 --> 00:23:16.500
What's that supposed to mean?

00:23:16.583 --> 00:23:19.461
So, this refers to the cerebrum.

00:23:19.961 --> 00:23:21.963
Humans were thought to respond to stimuli…

00:23:22.047 --> 00:23:24.216
SORRY. I DIDN'T MEAN FOR THAT TO HAPPEN.

00:23:24.299 --> 00:23:27.761
This is called behaviorism.

00:23:28.345 --> 00:23:34.100
In contrast, Tolman argued
that individuals react differently

00:23:34.184 --> 00:23:37.687
when the organism mediates
between stimulus and response.

00:23:38.438 --> 00:23:41.483
This is called neo-behaviorism.

00:23:41.566 --> 00:23:44.945
With this new theory,
each individual responds differently…

00:24:02.629 --> 00:24:03.630
Ryu.

00:24:05.549 --> 00:24:06.675
I need to talk to you.

00:24:08.927 --> 00:24:10.762
I just got a call.

00:24:14.391 --> 00:24:15.934
It's about Arata.

00:24:18.895 --> 00:24:20.105
He jumped.

00:24:23.733 --> 00:24:24.734
What?

00:24:25.652 --> 00:24:27.696
They took him to the hospital.

00:24:30.115 --> 00:24:32.284
I don't know the details yet.

00:24:38.790 --> 00:24:41.876
You know how we always went
to the public baths with him?

00:24:41.960 --> 00:24:43.086
Yeah.

00:24:43.169 --> 00:24:45.380
For him, the men's bath is like…

00:24:47.090 --> 00:24:48.383
You get what I'm saying?

00:24:48.883 --> 00:24:51.511
Yeah, it's like us going
in the women's bath.

00:24:51.595 --> 00:24:52.887
Exactly.

00:24:52.971 --> 00:24:54.764
-Isn't that crazy?
-Totally.

00:24:54.848 --> 00:24:57.475
-Should I give it a shot?
-You'll get caught.

00:25:29.758 --> 00:25:32.844
The person you are trying to reach
is unavailable.

00:25:32.927 --> 00:25:38.058
Please leave your name and message
after the tone.

00:25:40.310 --> 00:25:41.353
I'm sorry.

00:25:45.231 --> 00:25:46.316
I'm sorry.

00:25:49.361 --> 00:25:50.445
I'm really sorry.

00:25:53.365 --> 00:25:54.991
-Arata?
-Hey, Ryu!

00:25:55.575 --> 00:25:57.285
Where are you?

00:25:57.369 --> 00:25:59.037
The game's about to start!

00:26:00.372 --> 00:26:01.623
Hey, do you hear me?

00:26:02.123 --> 00:26:04.542
Ryu! Do you hear me?

00:26:17.097 --> 00:26:20.684
If, right now

00:26:20.767 --> 00:26:25.814
I can be true to my feelings

00:26:26.356 --> 00:26:30.568
My admiration

00:26:30.652 --> 00:26:34.781
And my love

00:26:34.864 --> 00:26:41.079
Will fly to the wide open sky

00:26:41.162 --> 00:26:44.040
And shine brightly

00:26:44.791 --> 00:26:48.962
I believe in future

00:26:49.045 --> 00:26:53.383
I believe

00:27:08.523 --> 00:27:11.401
I'M OFF TO SCHOOL.
EAT IT WHEN YOU'RE HUNGRY.

00:27:11.484 --> 00:27:12.694
FROM SUMIKO

00:27:25.790 --> 00:27:28.334
He's not Japanese. He's Korean.

00:27:29.335 --> 00:27:33.089
He's Korean. He's not from this country.

00:27:33.173 --> 00:27:36.843
There are signs that he tried to save you.

00:27:36.926 --> 00:27:40.680
He is a suspect,
but we don't know his motive.

00:27:41.264 --> 00:27:45.518
You said two people were arguing, right?

00:27:46.811 --> 00:27:48.730
He won't tell us anything.

00:27:49.314 --> 00:27:53.234
He won't tell us anything
about the other person.

00:27:53.318 --> 00:27:54.611
We're at a loss.

00:28:15.215 --> 00:28:16.216
Hey.

00:28:17.801 --> 00:28:18.718
Excuse me.

00:28:18.802 --> 00:28:19.803
What?

00:28:33.983 --> 00:28:36.528
Are you Japanese?

00:28:38.112 --> 00:28:39.113
Yes.

00:28:40.114 --> 00:28:41.825
Um…

00:28:45.578 --> 00:28:47.664
I know a bit of Japanese.

00:28:47.747 --> 00:28:49.791
Oh, I see.

00:28:51.376 --> 00:28:53.753
Thank you for saving me.

00:28:58.967 --> 00:29:00.051
It's nothing.

00:29:00.760 --> 00:29:01.761
Bye.

00:29:06.641 --> 00:29:07.559
Wait, um…

00:29:08.059 --> 00:29:11.437
Hold on. Hey.

00:29:11.521 --> 00:29:13.481
Um, the confession booth.

00:29:14.899 --> 00:29:16.150
At the church.

00:29:16.901 --> 00:29:20.905
You were on the other side, weren't you?

00:29:29.080 --> 00:29:31.833
That's none of your business. Got it?

00:29:31.916 --> 00:29:35.003
Well, that's true, but…

00:29:40.884 --> 00:29:43.136
What are you hoping for?

00:29:43.636 --> 00:29:46.139
-Hoping for?
-Yeah.

00:29:46.222 --> 00:29:48.391
What do you mean?

00:29:54.731 --> 00:29:58.484
Your sins have nothing to do with me.

00:30:00.403 --> 00:30:03.781
You're not even Christian, are you?

00:30:04.866 --> 00:30:05.867
Huh?

00:30:06.451 --> 00:30:07.452
I mean, um…

00:30:08.661 --> 00:30:11.706
The side you were sitting
is where the priest sits.

00:30:12.999 --> 00:30:14.083
Uh…

00:30:17.754 --> 00:30:20.506
Like I said, it's none of your business.

00:30:20.590 --> 00:30:21.591
Got it?

00:30:30.058 --> 00:30:34.020
Wait, did I do something to you?

00:30:39.901 --> 00:30:41.736
You didn't do anything.

00:30:42.487 --> 00:30:43.571
And neither did I.

00:30:44.656 --> 00:30:47.367
That's why I don't need your thanks.

00:30:52.080 --> 00:30:54.248
We just crossed paths in this city.

00:30:54.749 --> 00:30:57.835
We won't ever meet again, right?

00:31:09.555 --> 00:31:10.932
What a pathetic guy.

00:31:20.358 --> 00:31:22.276
-I'm back.
-Hey.

00:31:24.320 --> 00:31:26.155
-Sorry I left this.
-Hmm?

00:31:26.656 --> 00:31:30.535
That's totally fine. Where did you go?

00:31:32.286 --> 00:31:34.998
Hey, don't force yourself.

00:31:35.081 --> 00:31:37.792
You won't have room for dinner.

00:31:37.875 --> 00:31:40.461
It's okay. I can eat endlessly.

00:31:49.303 --> 00:31:50.847
I went to the police.

00:31:55.852 --> 00:31:58.479
I met the guy who saved me from the fire.

00:31:59.439 --> 00:32:01.899
Oh? What was he like?

00:32:04.861 --> 00:32:06.696
I'm not really sure.

00:32:08.031 --> 00:32:11.200
But he's totally different from me.

00:32:12.702 --> 00:32:13.536
I guess.

00:32:13.619 --> 00:32:16.164
-Oh?
-Yeah.

00:32:22.295 --> 00:32:23.504
I'll help.

00:32:23.588 --> 00:32:24.422
Okay.

00:32:25.339 --> 00:32:27.675
Thanks. In that case…

00:32:28.593 --> 00:32:30.803
Can you peel these?

00:32:32.722 --> 00:32:34.348
-Sure.
-Thank you.

00:32:42.690 --> 00:32:47.320
Well, we'll go watch
the boxing match tomorrow.

00:32:47.403 --> 00:32:50.531
Let's relieve our stress like, "Aaah!"

00:32:50.615 --> 00:32:52.700
You know, "Aaah!"

00:32:53.534 --> 00:32:55.995
-Go "Aaah"?
-Yeah, exactly.

00:32:56.662 --> 00:33:01.834
When I watched your ice hockey match
back in high school,

00:33:01.918 --> 00:33:06.255
you'd charge straight at
your opponents like, "Wham!"

00:33:06.339 --> 00:33:09.008
And I was like, "Aaah!"

00:33:09.509 --> 00:33:13.596
You took down huge guys
even though you weren't that buff.

00:33:13.679 --> 00:33:16.808
Watching you gave me courage.

00:33:59.725 --> 00:34:01.018
Ryu, over here.

00:34:12.822 --> 00:34:14.115
Excuse me.

00:34:50.526 --> 00:34:53.070
Hwang Johan!

00:34:55.072 --> 00:34:56.073
Huh?

00:34:57.909 --> 00:35:00.369
-Hmm?
-Nothing.

00:35:10.713 --> 00:35:15.384
The moment I stepped into the ring,
I tried not to look at the crowd.

00:35:16.177 --> 00:35:18.804
I had a feeling
that everything was about to begin.

00:35:19.555 --> 00:35:24.143
The joy, the pain, and the suffering.

00:35:24.227 --> 00:35:26.229
Don't get dragged into his rhythm.

00:35:26.312 --> 00:35:28.522
Stick to your boxing style, got it?

00:35:28.606 --> 00:35:29.815
Let's do this!

00:35:37.240 --> 00:35:39.700
Hwang Johan…

00:35:40.534 --> 00:35:44.622
On this day, our story begins.

00:37:55.628 --> 00:37:58.547
Subtitle translation by: Remi Miura